{
  "pattern": {
    "summary": "Fold an unsigned multiply-with-overflow followed by `overflow OR (truncated-product > constant)` into a single compare on the non-constant multiplicand.",
    "match": [
      "A call to `llvm.umul.with.overflow.*(X, C1)` or `llvm.umul.with.overflow.*(C1, X)` where `C1` is a non-zero integer constant or constant vector.",
      "Extract the product result `%mul = extractvalue %mwo, 0`.",
      "Extract the overflow flag `%ovf = extractvalue %mwo, 1`.",
      "Form `%cmp = icmp ugt %mul, C2` where `C2` is a constant of the same type as `%mul`.",
      "Form `%r = or i1 %ovf, %cmp` for scalar, or `or <N x i1> %ovf, %cmp` for vector. Operand order of the `or` is irrelevant."
    ],
    "rewrite": [
      "Replace `or %ovf, icmp ugt %mul, C2` with `icmp ugt X, udiv(C2, C1)`.",
      "For vectors, compute the division lane-wise when valid."
    ],
    "reasoning": "Let the full mathematical product be P = X * C1 in unsigned arithmetic, with `%mul` the low bits and `%ovf` indicating whether P exceeds the type range. The expression `(%ovf || (%mul > C2))` is true exactly when the full product P is greater than C2. For non-zero unsigned constant C1, `X * C1 > C2` is equivalent to `X > floor(C2 / C1)`.",
    "preconditions": [
      "The multiply intrinsic must be unsigned: `llvm.umul.with.overflow`.",
      "`C1 != 0` in every folded lane.",
      "The compare predicate is exactly `icmp ugt`.",
      "The compare must be against the extracted multiply result, not an arbitrary derived value.",
      "Only positive folds are listed here; implementation may additionally require one-use constraints to avoid duplication."
    ],
    "notes": [
      "If `C1 == 1`, the fold becomes `or ovf(false), icmp ugt X, C2` -> `icmp ugt X, C2`.",
      "If `C2` is the maximum unsigned value for the type, then `udiv(C2, C1)` is the largest X such that `X*C1 <= max`; the fold still holds and often becomes a pure overflow threshold test.",
      "The motivating example uses `C1 = 168`, `C2 = -16` on i64, i.e. `C2 = 18446744073709551600`, yielding `floor(C2/168) = 109802048057794950`."
    ]
  },
